The '''Toom clan''' was a criminal organization motivated solely by profit. The clan's headquarters was located in an underground base in [[Dorvalla/Legends|Dorvalla's]] northern wastes. They were originally a rescue operation which used [[Immobilizer 418 Interdictor-class Heavy Cruiser|Interdictor Cruisers]] to rescue those stranded in [[Realspace/Legends|space]], but soon moved on to [[Pirate/Legends|piracy]]. They survived by bribing the [[Dorvalla Space Corps]], which agreed to ignore their operation as long as they refrained from working within the [[Videnda sector/Legends|Videnda sector]].

In [[33 BBY/Legends|33 BBY]], the clan's leader was [[Nort Toom]]. The clan was made up largely of [[Weequay/Legends|Weequays]] and [[Nikto/Legends|Nikto]], with lesser numbers of [[Abyssin/Legends|Abyssin]], [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorreans]], [[Aqualish/Legends|Aqualish]], and [[Barabel/Legends|Barabels]].

The Toom clan was hired by both [[Lommite Limited]] and [[InterGalactic Ore]] to sabotage [[Ore/Legends|ore]] barges belonging to each other. Bold enough to carry out both contracts, The Toom Clan pulled the barges out of [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] using their Interdictor Cruisers, which caused the competing barges to collide over [[Eriadu/Legends|Eriadu]].

Both Lommite Limited and InterGalactic Ore were convinced that the clan had double crossed them. Shortly after the incident over [[Eriadu/Legends|Eriadu]], a small force composed of troops from both companies made an [[Raid on Riome|attack on the clan's lair]] on [[Riome]]. The Toom clan was unable to repel the attack and was defeated.

